The delinquents pasport [sic] or, A plaintiffs petitionary plea, addressed to an eminent counseller of state: upon his Highness Proclamation, commanding all delinquents, &c. to depart the Citty and return to their own native country.
1 sheet ([1] p.)
s.n., [London : 1657 [i.e. 1658]]
Imprint from Wing. Verse - "Confined Sir! For what? Where I do live". Includes: Additionall lines, in relation to these injunctive times. Annotation on Thomason copy: "March 1657". Imperfect: L (Luttrell) copy torn with loss of text. Reproduction of the originals in the British Library.
